gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 120, Timberwolves 109
gameRecap.excerpt: Anthony Davis becomes the first player in NBA history to put up 25+ points, 25+ rebounds, 5+ assists and 5+ steals in a game as the Lakers defeat the Timberwolves, 120-109. Davis put up 27 points, a season-high 25 rebounds, five assists, a career-high seven steals and three blocks for the Lakers, while LeBron James added a team-high 29 points, along with eight rebounds and nine assists in the victory. Naz Reid (25 points, five 3PM) and Anthony Edwards (25 points, seven rebounds, seven assists) combined for 50 points for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 36-30 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 44-21.
